obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40384)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774&sectionId=40384&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Government Buildings Act, 1899.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^1[the territories which, immediately before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States] ^2***.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `2 The word and rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 "and" the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40385)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `“Municipal authority” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774&sectionId=40385&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act the expression "municipal authority" includes`
  line `a municipal corporation or a body of municipal commissioners constituted by, or under the pro -`
  line `visions of, any law or enactment for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40386)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Exemption of certain Government buildings from municipal areas to regulate the erection, etc., of buildings within municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774&sectionId=40386&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in any law or enactment`
  line `for the time being in force to regulate the erection, re-erection, construction, alteration or`
  line `maintenance of buildings within the limits of any municipality shall apply to any building used`
  line `or required for the public service or for any public purpose, which is the property, or in the`
  line `occupation, of the Government, or which is to be erected on land which is the property, or in the`
  line `occupation, of the Government :`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the erection, re-erection, construction or material structural alteration of`
  line `any such building as aforesaid (not being a building connected with ^1*** defence, or a building`
  line `the plan or construction of which ought, in the opinion of ^2[the Government concerned], to be`
  line `treated as confidential or secret) is contemplated, reasonable notice of the proposed work shall be`
  line `given to the municipal authority before it is commenced.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Imperial" rep. by the A. O. 1948.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "the Govt.".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40387)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Objections or suggestions as to erection, etc., of certain Government buildings within municipalities, how to be made and dealt with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774&sectionId=40387&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_0_00036_189904_1523339193774
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of any such building as is`
  line `mentioned in the last preceding section (not being a building connected with ^1*** defence or a`
  line `building the plan or construction of which ought, in the opinion of ^2[the Government concerned],`
  line `to be treated as confidential or secret), the municipal authority, or any person authorized by it in`
  line `this behalf, may, with the permission of the State Government previously obtained, but not`
  line `otherwise, and subject to any restrictions or conditions which may, by general or special order, be`
  line `imposed by the State Government, inspect the land and building and all plans connected with its`
  line `erection, re-erection, construction or material structural alteration, as the case may be, and may`
  line `submit to the State Government a statement in writing of any objections or suggestions which such`
  line `municipal authority may deem fit to make with reference to such erection, re -erection, construction`
  line `or material structural alteration.`
  line
  line `(2) Every objection or suggestion submitted as aforesaid shall be considered by the State`
  line `Government, which shall, after such investigation (if any) as it shall think advisable, pass orders`
  line `thereon, and the building referred to therein shall be erected, re-erected, constructed or altered,`
  line `as the case may be, in accordance with such orders :`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the State Government overrules or disregards any such objection or suggestion as`
  line `aforesaid, it shall give its reasons for so doing in writing.`
  line
  line `^3* * *`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Imperial" rep. by the A. O. 1948.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "the Govt.".`
  line
  line `3 Sub-section (3) rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
